but I never agreed to anything.

260
00:11:06,140 --> 00:11:07,290
你们签了协议吗
Do you have a signed agreement?

261
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:12,790
没有
No.

262
00:11:12,860 --> 00:11:14,760
那我们准备开始模拟庭审吧
Then we are ready to proceed.

263
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:16,150
由你先开始
You have the floor.

264
00:11:16,170 --> 00:11:17,090
谢谢
Thank you.

265
00:11:18,530 --> 00:11:20,430
2010年3月31日
On March 31, 2010,

266
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:22,580
西德尼・汤普森对于自己电话被录音一事
Sydney Thompson was unwittingly recorded

267
00:11:22,580 --> 00:11:23,560
毫不知情
on a cell phone.

268
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:24,950
她开了个玩笑 
She made a joke,

269
00:11:24,950 --> 00:11:27,920
我相信法庭里的每个人 
the type of joke that I'm sure every person in this courtroom

270
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:29,850
都曾开过这样的玩笑
has made at one point or another...

271
00:11:42,350 --> 00:11:43,360
罗斯先生
Mr. Ross.

272
00:11:44,230 --> 00:11:45,720
罗斯先生
Mr. Ross!

273
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:49,110
你准备好了吗
Are you ready?

274
00:11:50,270 --> 00:11:53,280
被告方
Um, the, uh, the defense...

275
00:11:58,270 --> 00:12:00,190
根据波马斯特状告怀特里一案的结果
According to Bowmaster V. Whitely,

276
00:12:00,190 --> 00:12:02,060
如果一方当事人
if the party to a settlement is surprised

277
00:12:02,060 --> 00:12:03,810
突然得知和解被拒
by the repudiation of the settlement,

278
00:12:03,810 --> 00:12:06,340
那么法庭必须给出合理时限
then the court must provide a reasonable amount of time

279
00:12:06,340 --> 00:12:07,640
让其做好庭审准备
to prepare for the trial.

280
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:11,660
-合理时限  -是的  法官大人
- Reasonable time. - Yes, your honor.

281
00:12:11,660 --> 00:12:12,910
给你五分钟
You get five minutes.

282
00:12:14,470 --> 00:12:15,790
维加不止这些资产
Vega has more property.

283
00:12:15,830 --> 00:12:17,370
迪贝克更有潜力
Debeque has more potential.

284
00:12:18,340 --> 00:12:20,620
潜力很难用金钱来衡量
Which is harder to monetarily define.

285
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,370
这不是图书馆  斯科特
This isn't a library, Scottie.

286
00:12:22,370 --> 00:12:23,510
我的客户不懂并购
My guy's an up-and-comer.

287
00:12:23,510 --> 00:12:25,000
所以你的客户才会想搞突袭
That's why your guy's pouncing.

288
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:27,720
你的委托人是位冲动型购物者
Your client is an impulse shopper,

289
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,280
这就导致他成功得快
which is what may have made him a quick success,

290
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:31,310
但失败得也快
but it could make him an even faster failure.

291
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,450
他是个充满激情的人
So he's a passionate guy.

292
00:12:33,530 --> 00:12:36,110
他每爱上一座城市  就在那里建一座酒店
He falls in love with a city, and he builds himself a hotel.

293
00:12:36,170 --> 00:12:38,580
